To add the `eas build --local` command to your `package.json` scripts, you can modify the `scripts` section like this:

```json
{
  "name": "pausepoint",
  "version": "1.3.0",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "expo start --dev-client",
    "android": "expo run:android",
    "ios": "expo run:ios",
    "web": "expo start --web",
    "build:android": "eas build --platform android --local",
    "build:ios": "eas build --platform ios --local",
    "build:all": "eas build --platform all --local"
  }
  // ... rest of your package.json remains the same
}
```

After making this change:

1. You can run these simplified commands:

   - `npm run build:android` - to build Android APK locally
   - `npm run build:ios` - to build iOS app locally
   - `npm run build:all` - to build both platforms locally

2. Make sure you have:

   - EAS CLI installed globally (`npm install -g eas-cli`)
   - Run `eas build:configure` at least once to set up EAS
   - All required local build dependencies (Android Studio, Xcode, etc.)

3. For Android specifically, you'll need to:
   - Set up your Java environment
   - Configure your Android SDK
   - Set up signing keys for release builds

Would you like me to provide more detailed instructions for any of these setup steps?
